title: For Sale/Trade:  Norinco NHM 91
location: Dothan and surrounding area, Dothan, Alabama
postcontent:
Based on the Russian RPK light machine gun, the NHM features a stronger receiver and a longer, thicker-profile chrome-lined barrel measuring 20 inches (508mm) compared to the 590 mm (23.2 in) of the original RPK, along with a forward-mounted steel bipod.  Like the RPK, the NHM-91 utilizes a heavier-gauge stamped sheet metal receiver built from 1.5mm-thick stamped sheet metal instead of the 1mm thickness typical of a Soviet or Chinese-made AKM, resulting in increased rigidity, heavier weight, and improved overall accuracy. The longer, heavier barrel reduces shot dispersion and gives the NHM-91 a longer sight radius, again resulting in improved accuracy over the typical semi-auto AKM. Trigger pull weight is also lighter than other AK designs, and some users report the rifle capable of 2-2.5 minutes of angle accuracy or better with factory 7.62x39mm ammunition.  Stocks on the NHM-91 are of a one-piece thumbhole design with integral pistol grip, and are thicker and longer than the standard AKM/AK-47 buttstock the NHM-91 buttstock lacks a separate pistol grip, though the rifle may be retrofitted with a separate buttstock by simply cutting off the lower portion of the stock and grip with a band saw, OR install a third party stock and pistol grip then fitting a new pistol grip. Like its RPK counterpart, the NHM-91 does not come equipped from the factory with a bayonet lug. However, the front of the barrel is threaded and capped off with a thread protector. By removing the thread protector, a muzzle brake can be fitted.  Nice shooter, do not really want to sell but need to fund another rifle so this one and two others must go.

Comes with Rifle, factory installed bi pod, 2 factory 30 rd mag's, 1 5 rd mag, scope, 2 gun drag bag, 300 + rds ammo.

postcontent:
Weatherby 7MM REM Mark V Deluxe

NEW IN BOX.

DOES HAVE SMALL indent on right side of stock. 

24" Barrel
With Sights
Monte Carlo style stock
SN: H266712

The most famous of all Weatherby Rifles is the Mark V Deluxe. The most distinctive feature of any Weatherby rifle, and especially the Deluxe, is its unique Monte Carlo stock, designed specifically for powerful magnum calibers. Its comb slants down from back to front so that recoil moves the comb away from the shooter's face. Weatherby Deluxe stocks incorporate a cheek piece and a small amount of cast-off for quicker and more precise mounting. The butt area is generous, and the recoil pad is top quality. The forearm is cleverly shaped and tapers in three dimensions for a very secure grip under heavy recoil. The bottom of the forearm is essentially flat so that it is easy to shoot from a rest. Weatherby's wood stocks are reinforced with a steel bar in the pistol grip, and steel pins are located throughout the action mortise and epoxied in place to increase structural integrity.

The unique Weatherby stock was designed to look good, but also to minimize the recoil of powerful rifle cartridges. My impression, as the owner of a trio of Weatherby Deluxe magnum rifles, is that the weight of the rifle combined with the well shaped Weatherby stock really does minimize the effect of recoil. I find the Weatherby more pleasant to shoot from a bench rest than any other production bolt action rifle of comparable power.

The Mark V Deluxe features a select Clara walnut stock with a rosewood forearm tip and grip cap set off by line spacers made from thin slices of maplewood. The pistol grip and forearm are checkered in a French skip-line point pattern, and there is a maplewood diamond inlay in the pistol grip cap. A durable high gloss finish shows off the wood to maximum advantage.

It is a strikingly handsome stock, but the careful observer will also note that the inletting and bedding are very precisely done. There are no wood to metal gaps, and the barrel is not free floating.

The Deluxe action is polished and metal work receives the famous high luster Weatherby blue. In 2006 the Mark V Deluxe was offered in Weatherby Magnum calibers .257, .270, 7mm, .300, .340, .30-378, .416, and .460. Cartridge capacity is 3+1 for most calibers and 2+1 for Weatherby Magnum calibers based on the huge .378 case. The Deluxe is a very classy rifle, and a rather expensive one. MSRP in 2006 starts at $2063 for calibers from .257 to .340, and runs $2428-$2853 for calibers based on .378 case.

Per my bathroom scale, it weighs 6.4 pounds (unloaded).  

I also built this rifle to be (mostly) ambidextrous, with the Troy Industries ambidextrous selector switch, MagPul B.A.D. Lever, and the Rainier Arms Ambidextrous Raptor Charging Handle.  The only non-ambidextrous function is the magazine release.

Additionally, this rifle has a high quality Geissele SD-3G flat trigger in it, making every trigger pull a smooth dream, with awesome reset.  If you have shot a mil-spec AR-15, you know the trigger can be a little rough - the Geissele trigger makes shooting an AR a hundred times better.

The Troy front and rear folding sights are some of the best on the market, but this gun would be even better with a cool optic (maybe something like a lightweight Aimpoint Micro?).


Here are the rifle specs -

- MagPul MOE Stock, Mil-Spec, flat dark earth

- Rainier Arms Raptor Ambidextrous Charging Handle 

- MagPul Battery Assist Device (B.A.D.) Lever 

- Tango Down Battle Grip BG-16, black 

- CMMG Lower Parts Kit 

- Troy Industries Ambidextrous Safety Selector

- Geissele SD-3G Super Dynamic 3 Gun Trigger 

- Sig Sauer M400 upper receiver, Cerakoted in MagPul flat dark earth, with Sig Sauer bolt carrier group, 16 inch barrel

- Troy Industries Front Folding Battle Sight, M4 Style, flat dark earth 

- Troy Industries Rear Folding Battle Sight, FBS-R, flat dark earth 

- Twenty-three (23) LaRue Tactical index clips, flat dark earth

- Fortis Rail QD Attachment Point

- Midwest Industries Low-Profile Gas Block 

- Midwest Industries Gen. 2 SS-Series Free Float Modular Rail Handguard, Extended Carbine, flat dark earth

- Primary Weapons Systems Tactical Compensator and Flash Suppressor

This rifle is (in my opinion, obviously) awesome, and really fun to shoot.  I am asking $1,500.00 (OBO) for the rifle, for sale face to face in New Hampshire.

I am willing to entertain offers, but please *think* before you send an offer.  I will not take $800.00 for the rifle  if you want a cheap plinking rifle, look elsewhere.  I am not interested in your rusty snowmobile.  I want cash or firearms related items ONLY.  In fact, I am specifically looking for the following:

-	Heckler & Koch P30 in 9mm with LEM trigger
-	Bushmaster ACR, enhanced, preferably in Coyote
-	FN SCAR 16S, preferably in Flat Dark Earth
-	Qualify manufacture (except Kimber) 1911 in 9mm or .45 ACP

I am also always looking for anything firearms related that is interesting or unique.  I am interested almost exclusively in modern firearms, so a newer .308 bolt gun might get my attention, but an old .30-30 lever action probably will not.

I am willing to add, or work with, any deal to make it work.  I have other items I can add to include slings, gear, optics, lights, magazines, and/or ammunition.  Please feel free to contact me with any questions.  Again, thank your for looking and reading through my listing.

title: For Sale:  Classic 1949 Marlin 336 RC 30-30 Ballard Pre-microgroove 336RC -Best Offer
postcontent:
Classic Marlin Lever-action 30-30 for sale. All original finish is a uniform patina, excellent for a period piece. The entire rifle has been disassembled for inspection and thorough cleaning/oiling and there is no rust or pitting on any metal surface -even under the wood stock.

This rifle was manufactured a few years before Marlin switched to the current Microgroove line of barrels. Traditional Ballard rifling is preferable for those who shoot non-jacketed bullets. There are not many classic Pre-microgroove Marlin 30-30's to choose from these days.

The action on this rifle is smooth, the lever locks up tight, and a test firing both Remington Core-lokt and Winchester SuperX ammo produced consistent groups at 100 yards. No failures-to-fire nor failure-to-feed.

Please include your phone number if you want me to reply. I may not know your message is not spam robot emails otherwise. Face to face sale with a legal AZ resident only -no tax.

If you are reading this, the rifle is still available. Ad will be pulled immediately upon sale so no need to ask. Thank you for your interest. I am in Bisbee but do go to Tucson on business. Feel free to contact me with your best cash offer.
